    "department": "Client Service",
    "description": "Who We Are:\n\nSequoia is the strategic partner helping investor-backed companies of all sizes achieve their business goals through smarter people spend. For 24 years, we’ve guided the most innovative employers to navigate growth and get the most out of their global people investment. With our expert advisory team and integrated platform, we help clients drive business impact through their total comp and benefits, improving executive decision making, controlling costs, protecting the business, and elevating the employee experience. Visit Sequoia.com http://Sequoia.com or follow us on LinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/company/sequoia-tpi/%22%20/t%20%22_blank to learn more.\n\nWhat You Get to Do:\n\nAs a Market Analyst, you will play a critical role in supporting operations by handling key client tasks, delivering efficient workflows, maintaining accurate records, and ensuring the success of our mid-enterprise group markets. This role focuses on non-client-facing duties, involving handling policy documentation, managing client records, and supporting client service deliverables. You will also partner with cross-functional teams on impactful client deliverables and play an essential role in our benefits renewal cycle.\n\n• Monitor competitors and market positioning to inform strategic initiatives.\n\n• Work directly with our insurance carrier partners to ensure accurate policy issuance and updates.\n\n• Process, organize, and maintain client files, policy documents, and claims data.\n\n• Conduct regular audits to verify the accuracy of client and policy records.\n\n• Handle sensitive information with confidentiality and discretion.\n\n• Generate reports on policy renewals, claims status, and other metrics.\n\n• Monitor policy renewals and assist in the collection of renewals.\n\n• Manage and organize client documentation, records, and databases.\n\n• Process and verify data for accuracy and completeness.\n\n• Prepare and submit RFP’s and manage RFP responses.\n\n• Coordinate with other departments to ensure seamless operations.\n\n• Enter, update, and maintain records in spreadsheets or databases.\n\n• Generate reports for analysis and decision-making.\n\n• Act as a liaison between departments to facilitate information flow.\n\n• Handle correspondence such as emails, letters, and internal memos.\n\n• Support in maintaining confidentiality and security of sensitive information.\n\n• Provide administrative support for special projects or initiatives.\n\nWhat You Bring:\n\nYou are a highly detail-oriented and organized professional with the ability to handle multiple projects and workstreams at once. Your expertise in analysis, combined with your strong administration and project management skills, will drive success for our clients and the organization.\n\n• Bachelor's degree in Business, Marketing, Economics, or a related field.\n\n• 5+ years of experience.\n\n• 2-3+ years in administration, internal customer service, analysis or a related field.\n\n• Prior experience working in financial services, consulting, or healthcare is highly desired.\n\n• Proven ability to create and maintain systems for delivering white glove customer service.\n\n• Exceptional project management skills with a track record of managing complex processes.\n\n• Excellent communication and interpersonal skills to collaborate across teams and with clients.\n\n• Ability to manage multiple priorities, meet deadlines, and maintain high-quality work.\n\n• A proactive mindset with a passion for staying ahead of industry trends and ensuring client success.\n\n• English Proficiency.\n\nSequoia’s Culture – Our most important asset \n\n - Integrity \n\n - Passion for service \n\n - Innovative \n\n - Growth oriented \n\n - Caring for others \n\n - Promise-centric \n\n - Focused on relationship building \n\nSequoia provides equal opportunity to all applicants without regard to race, color, creed, religion, citizenship, national origin, age, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, pregnancy, marital status, military or veteran status, disability, or any other basis prohibited by applicable law.\n\nCompensation \u0026 Benefits\nSequoia provides competitive compensation including base salary, performance-based bonus programs, and comprehensive benefits package.\n\nSequoia’s Candidate Privacy Policy \n\nhttps://www.sequoia.com/legal/candidate-privacy-policy/ ",
